## Why use manipulatives to build a shared mental model?

#### Here are just a few reasons why we've included shared mental models in the curriculum:
##
* ##### **Mental models can build over time**. Explore lessons often use the same materials to demonstrate coding concepts. By reusing these manipulatives, students can revisit what they've already learn to evolve their understanding of computer science throughout the year.

* ##### **Memorable experiences are one way we build CS understanding with equity in mind.** We want to give students memorable experiences in programming units. One way we do this is through using mental models that provide all students, regardless of prior programming experience, a solid foundation in a concept.

* ##### **Having a shared mental model means you have a tool in your teaching toolbox.** After every student has a shared mental model they can talk to one another with this in mind. When working with students, you can reference the mental model to help clear up misconceptions.
